<!-- ── FAQ ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section" id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="center">
      <div class="tag">FAQ</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Questions manufacturing teams usually ask first</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">These are the practical questions most teams ask before they move from spreadsheets and separate tools into one ERP.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details class="faq-item" open>
        <summary>Is Factory SaaS only for inventory and payroll?</summary>
        <p>No. Inventory and payroll are common entry points, but the platform also covers procurement, production, BOMs, work orders, QC, delivery, invoicing, vendor management, finance, HR, and reporting.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can multiple factories use the same platform?</summary>
        <p>Yes. Factory SaaS is designed as a multi-tenant system, so each factory or company stays isolated while admins still get clean operational oversight.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How does it connect sales, production, and delivery?</summary>
        <p>The platform supports a connected flow from sales order to BOM and work order creation, QC, delivery challan, invoice, and profitability review.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can we migrate our current Excel and manual data?</summary>
        <p>Yes. We help with onboarding and data migration so teams can move employee, inventory, and core operational records into the system faster.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Who typically uses it inside the factory?</summary>
        <p>Owners, admins, production managers, procurement teams, warehouse staff, finance teams, HR teams, and quality teams can all use it with role-based access control.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

